
Steps to preparing the HOST PC and install Yocto for SMARC + eNUC (ROJ demokit):

1) download Ubuntu 16.04
2) download VirtualBox and setup Virtual Machine (VM)
3) install Ubuntu 16.04 in your VM
4) check that VM is connected to internet (mandatory)
5) install git with the command: sudo apt-get install git
6) clone tools repo with the command: git clone https://github.com/ROJ-ITALY/tools.git -b morty (*1)
7) change dir to tools (cd tools) and run these scripts in this order:
	a) ./download_packages
	b) ./create-yocto-environment

Below the steps to configuring Yocto for ROJ demokit:

SMARC based on i.MX6 Quad/Dual
	a) cd $HOME/yocto-enuc-morty
	b) MACHINE=imx6qenuc DISTRO=fsl-imx-fb source ./fsl-setup-release.sh -b bld_qd_enuc (*2)
	c) replace the content of the file bld_qd_enuc/conf/bblayers.conf with bblayers-roj-platform.conf
	d) replace the content of the file bld_qd_enuc/conf/local.conf with local-qd.conf (*3)

SMARC based on i.MX6 Quad (RAM 2GB --> NEW!)
	a) cd $HOME/yocto-enuc-morty
	b) MACHINE=imx6qenuc DISTRO=fsl-imx-fb source ./fsl-setup-release.sh -b bld_qd_enuc (*2)
	c) replace the content of the file bld_qd_enuc/conf/bblayers.conf with bblayers-roj-platform.conf
	d) replace the content of the file bld_qd_enuc/conf/local.conf with local-quad-2GB.conf (*3)

SMARC based on i.MX6 solo (RAM 512MB)
	a) cd $HOME/yocto-enuc-morty
	b) MACHINE=imx6soloenuc DISTRO=fsl-imx-fb source ./fsl-setup-release.sh -b bld_solo_enuc (*2)
	c) replace the content of the file bld_solo_enuc/conf/bblayers.conf with bblayers-roj-platform.conf
	d) replace the content of the file bld_solo_enuc/conf/local.conf with local-solo.conf (*3)

SMARC based on i.MX6 solo (RAM 1GB)
	a) cd $HOME/yocto-enuc-morty
	b) MACHINE=imx6soloenuc DISTRO=fsl-imx-fb source ./fsl-setup-release.sh -b bld_solo_enuc (*2)
	c) replace the content of the file bld_solo_enuc/conf/bblayers.conf with bblayers-roj-platform.conf
	d) replace the content of the file bld_solo_enuc/conf/local.conf with local-solo-1GB.conf (*3)

---------------------	
Note:
(*1) Tools dir contains some useful shell scripts in order to prepare the Host system to use Yocto Project.

(*2) You have to run this command only the first time; for the next times is sufficient enter:
		source ./setup-environment bld_qd_enuc
	 or
		source ./setup-environment bld_solo_enuc

(*3) Set DL_DIR (DownLoad DIRectory) variable in local.conf with your local path.
	 For example: DL_DIR ?= "/home/xxx/downloads/" where "xxx" is your user.

